#####  open a new terminal and tail alert log file. #######
cd /u01/app/oracle/diag/rdbms/proddb/proddb/trace/
ls -lrt alert_proddb.log
tail -f alert_proddb.log

###############################
create user SCOTT:
connect to sys user and execute below script:
https://github.com/vamshireddy257/OracleDBA/blob/main/create_scott

verify if scott user is create?
select username from dba_users where username = 'SCOTT';
###############################

###############################
shut down normal:START
###############################
connect to scott from 2 sessions:
from one of those initiate DML:

now issue command
shutdown normal;

and observe that instance is not closed when those two sessions are still connected to the instance. 
###############################
shut down normal: END
###############################

###############################
shut down transactional:START
###############################
connect to scott from 2 sessions:
from one of those initiate DML:

now issue command
shutdown transactional;
and observe that instance is not closed till all the transactions are completed. 
###############################
shut down transactional:END
###############################


###############################
shut down immediate :START
###############################
connect to scott from 2 sessions:
from one of those initiate DML:

now issue command
shutdown immediate;
and observe that instance is closed immediatly and all the sessions are terminated.
And there is a checkpoint which writes pending commited data from database buffer cache to respective datafiles.
And then the instance is closed gracefully. 
select current_scn,checkpoint_change# from v$database;

###############################
shut down immediate :end
###############################


###############################
shut down abort :START
###############################
connect to scott from 2 sessions:
from one of those initiate DML and commit:
from other initiate DML and leave it:


now issue command
shutdown obort;
and observe that instance is closed immediatly and all the sessions are terminated.
And there is a NO NO NO checkpoint which writes pending commited data from database buffer cache to respective datafiles.
And then the instance is terminated. 

###############################
shut down abort :end
###############################
